This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses active learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. It also mentions deep learning, which is a popular topic in the machine learning community. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the experiments are conducted on image datasets (CIFAR-10 and CIFAR-100) and the paper discusses the use of active learning in image classification tasks. 

Additionally, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible sub-category as active learning is a technique used in various AI applications. 

cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible sub-category as the paper discusses the use of active learning in natural language processing tasks, such as text classification. 

Finally, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible sub-category as the paper proposes a new class of active learning methods based on sequential-based algorithms, which involves designing efficient algorithms for data processing.
